Adult.description: Blue Jays have a crest that Florida Scrub-Jays don't have. They also have blue backs and a white wingbar unlike the gray-backed and plain-winged Florida Scrub-Jay.

Adult (Woodhouse's).description: Woodhouse's Scrub-Jays look very similar, but they don't have the white frosting on the forehead like Florida Scrub-Jays. Their range does not overlap with the Florida Scrub-Jay.

Adult.description: California Scrub-Jays look similar, but they lack the Florida Scrub-Jay's white frosting on the forehead. Their ranges do not overlap.
